Sentencas: A mathematical model of electrochemical processes in a solid oxide fuel cell is presented.
Titulo: Modeling of electrochemical processes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A procedure for the calculation of the current-voltage characteristic (CVC) taking into account the influence of the reagent concentration, pressure, and temperature is considered.
Titulo: Modeling of electrochemical processes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The problem of calculation of the electromotive force (emf) and thermodynamic efficiency was studied in detail.
Titulo: Modeling of electrochemical processes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The influence of the presence of carbon dioxide and water vapor in the anode gas on the emf and thermodynamic efficiency is analyzed.
Titulo: Modeling of electrochemical processes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The method of measuring the CVC in an experiment at a constant fuel rate is briefly considered.
Titulo: Modeling of electrochemical processes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results of application of the calculation model are compared with the experimental data.
Titulo: Modeling of electrochemical processes in solid oxide fuel cells
